 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">We first calculate the energy levels under the harmonic approximation. We compare this to the energy levels obtained with a fourth order expansion of the potential. The results for H
  <sub>2</sub>O are shown in 
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="fig2" href="#fig2">Fig. 2</a>. We can see that although the ground state can be well approximated by the harmonic oscillators, the excited states deviate from the harmonic oscillators at higher energy levels. The results for SO
  <sub>2</sub> can be found in the Appendix. These calculations highlight the importance of anharmonic terms in the potential for even small molecules.
 </p>
